# Project: Grocery Tracker

Build a personal grocery and vegetables reminder app 
for **your favorite platform: android/ios/mac/win/linux/web**.

The app should let me add items (like rice, oil, onions, tomatoes, etc.) 
along with the quantity I purchased. 

Based on my usage, the app should automatically calculate when 
those items will run out and remind me before running out.

The app is offline-first.

The app should save all data locally. Using a local SQLite database (android). 
It should track purchase history and estimate how many days each item usually lasts. 
Using this data, the app should predict the next time Iâ€™ll need to buy that item again.

Features I want:
- Add grocery/vegetable items with name, quantity, unit (kg, litres, etc.)
- Save each purchase with date & quantity
- Track current quantity
- Automatically estimate daily usage
- Predict when an item will run out
- Show a "To Buy Soon" list
- Give reminders/notifications before the item finishes
- Run background checks even if the app is closed
- Everything works offline (data saved locally on device)

Technologies I'm planning to use (android):
- React Native (Bare Workflow)
- SQLite for local storage
- Notifee for notifications
- react-native-background-fetch for background reminders

The goal is to have a simple, smart, offline grocery assistant 
that helps me remember when to buy items before they finish.

